A Businessman was on Tuesday arraigned for allegedly assaulting a 14 year old minor in Kilimani area in Nairobi. Edwin Njiru Kareithi was arraigned before Kibera senior principal magistrate Philip Mutua when the matter came up for mention. The accused person committed the offence on August 9 at Riara valley garden within Nairobi County. He denied the charges and was released on Sh 10,000 bond. Court prosecutor Jane  Gitahi  told the court that the suspect will be  supplied documentary evidences and witness statements for the case to proceed on September 15 where the minor is set to testify.